    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, peel and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Combine your <strong>mayo </strong>and<strong> grated garlic </strong>(not a big garlic fan? Try using less!) in a small bowl with <strong>half</strong> your <strong>white wine vinegar </strong>(you'll use the rest later!) and the<strong> remaining dried oregano</strong></p><p>Add<strong> </strong>1/2 tsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[3/4 tsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[1 tsp]</span><strong> sugar </strong>and a small pinch of <strong>salt </strong> – this is your <strong>garlic dip</strong></p>",
